key "savary1998effect,dardevet1999glucocorticoid-induced"

\end_inset

.
 In cell cultures, Dexa inhibition of protein synthesis should be more readily
 detectable, given that, in vitro, Dexa affects 4E-BP phosphorylation directly,
 even in basal state
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citep
key "shah2000glucocorticoidsa"

\end_inset

.
 However, studies are similarly equivocal.
 In the most glaring example, the same group, using the same methods and
 working on the same L6 line, found that protein synthesis is 
